<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation" TextAlignment="Justify"
    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">
 
<Paragraph Style="{DynamicResource HeaderParagraphStyle}">
This section contains samples that demonstrate adding security to a PDF document using Essential PDF.
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph>
Here is a list of samples with descriptions.
</Paragraph>
<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Digital Signature</Bold> - This sample demonstrates how a PDF document can be secured with certificates and signed with either standard or author signatures.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Encryption</Bold> - This sample demonstrates how a PDF document can be protected with user and owner passwords, and how it can restrict users from accessing some functionalities, such as printing.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Redaction</Bold> - This sample demonstrates the redaction of PDF documents. Redaction is used to remove confidential information from PDF document.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>
</FlowDocument>
